1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:16,000
 Hvala misusi Marija, dragi pratitelji YouTube kanala Udruge Hrvatska za život.

2
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:22,000
 Mi se ovdje nalazimo na Trešnjevci u župi Svetog Josipa Radnika u njihovim prostorijama,

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:30,000
 budući da ovog vikenda imamo konferenciju za život, život dakle biraj, šestu u organizaciji naše udruge.

4
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,000
 Jedna odgovornica biće i Ruth Rawlings iz Ujedinjeno Kraljevstva.

5
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:45,000
 Danas ćemo s njom razgovarati, razgovor ćemo vojiti na engleskom jeziku, pa ćete imati dolje titlove za one koji možda neće dobro razumijeti. Počnimo.

6
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,000
 Hi Ruth.

7
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,000
 Hi Lydia.

8
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:54,000
 I'm so happy to have you here, thank you for coming to our conference and here in our podcast.

9
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,000
 It's wonderful to be here.

10
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:01,000
 I would love that you introduce yourself so people know with whom we are talking to.

11
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:06,000
 Okay, so I'm Ruth Rawlings and I've come all the way from London, England,

12
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:14,000
 and I work in communications for the Centre for Bioethical Reform UK, CBR UK for short.

13
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:27,000
 And we're basically working to educate on the humanity of the baby in the womb and expose the reality of abortion and support women who have been through abortion.

14
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:36,000
 Okay, so our podcasts are something like testimony and spiritual talk and also official talk.

15
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:46,000
 Can you please tell us something about your background, childhood, religion and everything and how did you get involved in the pro-life moment?

16
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:55,000
 Okay, so I grew up in a Christian home and I never really heard anything about abortion at church.

17
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,000
 It wasn't spoken about.

18
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:07,000
 I remember in school, in religious studies, we did talk about abortion and writing an essay about it.

19
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:17,000
 And actually, funnily enough, I found that essay recently and I noticed that I had written a rape exception, which is interesting.

20
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:25,000
 My views have clearly changed now. But my parents had put across to me that abortion was wrong.

21
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:30,000
 So I knew that it wasn't a good thing. I knew that it was killing a baby.

22
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:35,000
 And fast forward to when I went to university, I actually walked away from the Lord.

23
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:43,000
 I think I thought the grass was greener on the other side, if that saying makes sense in Croatian.

24
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:49,000
 And I, yeah, I just got into a bad relationship, an ungodly relationship.

25
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000
 I ended up becoming pregnant in my final year of university.

26
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:59,000
 And because I knew that abortion was wrong, it didn't enter my head.

27
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:07,000
 And I'm so grateful to God and to my parents for that, because otherwise, you know, my child might not be here today.

28
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:12,000
 And so that was my path of coming back to God.

29
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:20,000
 I when I had my baby dedicated at church and then I got baptized the next month.

30
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:30,000
 And so, yeah, it was obviously having a daughter and being a single mother had some challenges that came with that.

31
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:44,000
 But it was an exciting time for me because I was discovering more and more about God and fellowship in with lots of other parents and children, mothers and children at that time.

32
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:48,000
 So I enjoyed those years of raising my daughter up.

33
00:03:48,000 --> 00:04:00,000
 And I, the issue of abortion came back into my life when I was working for my church for a year, I was doing a voluntary year at my church.

34
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:06,000
 And I came in because at my church, they used to rent out rooms to the local council.

35
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:14,000
 And there was a sign on the door and it said pregnancy decision making meeting in room three.

36
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:24,000
 And my heart was grieved. What decisions are there to be made in pregnancy and why is this being held in a church?

37
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:34,000
 And when I spoke to the people at the church who worked in administration, they said, you don't know what it is they're talking about.

38
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:43,000
 But I knew it was abortion. And at that moment, I had to find a quiet room and I just wept.

39
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:47,000
 And I think the Lord really wept through me.

40
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:53,000
 And I felt my heart break for the issue for the babies that are being killed.

41
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,000
 And I felt the heart of God actually in that moment.

42
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:06,000
 And I started reading about the life of William Wilberforce and was really inspired because he wrote down his two life goals.

43
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:09,000
 One was to see an end to the transatlantic slave trade.

44
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:22,000
 Now William Wilberforce was the politician in the UK and he was he's been credited actually in history for being fundamental in ending the transatlantic slave trade.

45
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:29,000
 So he wrote that down as one of his goals. And so I decided to write down my goals and ending abortion was one of them.

46
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:40,000
 But that stayed in my journal for a couple of years. I didn't really do anything until I saw a program, a conference called the Wilberforce Academy.

47
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:45,000
 And they were talking about abortion. So I knew I had to be there and I went along.

48
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:54,000
 And at that conference, I met my now boss from CBR UK and they showed us a video of an abortion procedure.

